	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A full bench in the North Gauteng High Court has granted former President Jacob Zuma the right to intervene in the leave to appeal the state capture report case. This means that the former president may now apply for leave to appeal the personal costs order against him, which was an order made by the same court in December last year, after the court dismissed Zuma’s review application of the public protector’s report. More to follow. READ: Presidency leaves Zuma to pick up state capture report court costs  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  